{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-projects-js","path":"/projects/","result":{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"543a1802-7a56-5492-aafc-76f63f147834","html":"<p>A web-based judging solution for hackathons.</p>\n<p>Ballot allows hackathon organizers to get the most out of a potentially limited number of judges. Projects are assigned to judges dynamically based on a series of configurable parameters, including overall score, score range, and number of visits. Projects can also be assigned manually using the same interface, with the goal of getting each project as many judges as it needs to get an accurate ranking.</p>\n<p>Judges can judge projects for one or many categories. They can also mark a project as busy or missing.</p>\n<p>Expo tables are automatically assigned based on number of expos, number of table groups, and number of tables. Automatic assignment can be overriden if projects need certain tables.</p>\n<p>Ballot was used at HackGT 5 and 6, each with 1000+ participants, 30+ judges, and 200+ projects across 2 hour-long expos.</p>","frontmatter":{"endDate":"Oct 2019","startDate":"Jul 2019","title":"HackGT: Ballot (V2)","type":"project","link":"https://github.com/HackGT/ballot","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7241379310344827,"src":"/static/3d8e33be082b61416a7d3fe19b71136a/31987/ballot.png","srcSet":"/static/3d8e33be082b61416a7d3fe19b71136a/e1953/ballot.png 250w,\n/static/3d8e33be082b61416a7d3fe19b71136a/46604/ballot.png 500w,\n/static/3d8e33be082b61416a7d3fe19b71136a/31987/ballot.png 1000w,\n/static/3d8e33be082b61416a7d3fe19b71136a/4e4ad/ballot.png 1439w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"b110f3b1-60cf-52ea-919c-0e77c8b19205","html":"<p>An Electron application written to allow HackGT organizers to clock-in to events and general meetings with a tap or swipe of their student IDs.</p>\n<p>Graphical clock-in uses colorful, full-screen status screens with sound (heavily inspired by <a href=\"https://youtu.be/X0HrYB9zoME?t=9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Ventra readers in Chicago</a>) to provide a full self-service experience.</p>\n<p>This integrates with Georgia Tech's OrgSync and Engage platforms (through non-public APIs) to monitor and track attendance for meetings and events.</p>\n<p>Due to privacy concerns, I cannot provide the source code.</p>","frontmatter":{"endDate":"Feb 2019","startDate":"Jan 2019","title":"Graphical Clock-in","type":"project","link":null,"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7730496453900708,"src":"/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/31987/clockin.png","srcSet":"/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/e1953/clockin.png 250w,\n/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/46604/clockin.png 500w,\n/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/31987/clockin.png 1000w,\n/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/0dadc/clockin.png 1500w,\n/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/ed396/clockin.png 2000w,\n/static/b0fb3d6333b226e8aaf065330f604c44/96fcf/clockin.png 3840w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"b7e69867-0a51-558b-8850-9f0f565722db","html":"<p>An interactive bus map for the Hampton Roads region.</p>\n<p>This was a project created for <em>SLS 3110: Technology and Sustainable Communites</em> at Georgia Tech to help visualize the (often convoluted) bus routes in the region.</p>\n<p>We worked closely with Garry A. Harris, the President of the Center for Sustainable Communities, to move Cavalier Manor, a neighborhood in Portsmouth, VA, closer to becoming an EcoDistrict.</p>\n<p>The application itself uses Google's GTFS to display lines and routes. A user can see what service looks like on a weekday vs a weekend, and it will highlight the selected routes.</p>","frontmatter":{"endDate":"Dec 2018","startDate":"Oct 2018","title":"Hampton Roads Bus Map","type":"project","link":"https://github.com/NameThatFollows/CavalierBus","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7730496453900708,"src":"/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/31987/cavalierbus.png","srcSet":"/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/e1953/cavalierbus.png 250w,\n/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/46604/cavalierbus.png 500w,\n/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/31987/cavalierbus.png 1000w,\n/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/0dadc/cavalierbus.png 1500w,\n/static/81afe9e6eeb9c94d37cdd15923a8b268/eeb1b/cavalierbus.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"9554b213-0a24-54cd-963b-9bfca19f86aa","html":"<p>A self-service portal for Hershey High School National Honor Society members, officers, and advisors.</p>\n<p>This portal allows Hershey's NHS members to access their tracked service hours, yearly requirements, event signups, important forms, and other important information.</p>\n<p>Officers and advisors can edit website content, add/edit/remove event signups, and service hours for each member.</p>\n<p>This website has been used by 600+ students since initial launch and is still currently being used in production.</p>\n<p>The source of truth for the site is stored separately from the internal database for simplicity. Similarly, passwords are stored in plain text since the site stores no sensitive information.</p>","frontmatter":{"endDate":"Feb 2018","startDate":"Jan 2018","title":"Hershey NHS Website","type":"project","link":"https://github.com/NameThatFollows/hersheynhs","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2,"src":"/static/459f4e36241fc585cdd5d821de38fe7e/a7715/hersheynhs.jpg","srcSet":"/static/459f4e36241fc585cdd5d821de38fe7e/8f7df/hersheynhs.jpg 250w,\n/static/459f4e36241fc585cdd5d821de38fe7e/0f3a1/hersheynhs.jpg 500w,\n/static/459f4e36241fc585cdd5d821de38fe7e/a7715/hersheynhs.jpg 1000w,\n/static/459f4e36241fc585cdd5d821de38fe7e/1abfa/hersheynhs.jpg 1366w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}}}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}